Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Indiana Convention Center, expressing her gratitude to the National Board of Directors of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority and the members of Delta Sigma Theta. She praised Marcia Fudge for her leadership and highlighted the accomplishments of the Biden administration, such as capping the cost of insulin for seniors, addressing lead pipe issues, investing in HBCUs, and prioritizing maternal health. Harris also addressed challenges the country is facing, including attacks on women's reproductive rights, voting restrictions, discrimination against marginalized communities, lack of gun safety laws, and book bans. She called on the leaders in the room to continue fighting for what is right and to stand together in the face of these challenges.